FBIS3-53756 "drnes012_l_94006" FBIS-NES-94-012 Document Type:Daily Report 19 Jan 1994 ISRAEL Peres, 'Arafat To Discuss Taba Talks in Oslo 22 Jan TA1801202794 Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network in Hebrew 1800 GMT 18 Jan 94 TA1801202794 Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network in Hebrew 1800 GMT 18 Jan 94 Language: Hebrew Article Type:BFN [Text] Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres will meet with PLO Chairman Yasir 'Arafat in Oslo. The meeting will take place after the funeral of Norwegian Foreign Minister Johan Jorgen Holst on Saturday [22 January]. U.S. Secretary of State Warren Christopher is also slated to attend the funeral. The meeting was arranged in a conversation held in recent days between Peres and 'Arafat's adviser, Dr. Ahmad al-Tibi, and in contacts between Foreign Ministry Director General Uri Savir and PLO official Abu-al-'Ala'. Unless tangible developments occur before their meeting, Peres and 'Arafat will attempt to advance the Taba talks.
